- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely because the paper discusses the use of a deformation-based mesh representation and a coarse-to-fine reconstruction pipeline, which are common techniques in computer graphics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely because the paper proposes an autoencoder-like network architecture to learn disentangled shape and pose embeddings, which is a common machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely because the paper deals with learning representations of human bodies, which is a common topic in AI research related to human-like agents and robotics. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible because the paper deals with 3D human body models, which are commonly used in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and gaming.
